{"id":38320,"date":"2024-05-03T10:57:09","date_gmt":"2024-05-03T15:57:09","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/altamira.edu.co\/?post_type=project&#038;p=38320"},"modified":"2024-05-03T11:46:58","modified_gmt":"2024-05-03T16:46:58","slug":"plogg-for-the-planet","status":"publish","type":"project","link":"https:\/\/altamira.edu.co\/project\/plogg-for-the-planet\/","title":{"rendered":"Plogg for the planet"},"content":{"rendered":"[et_pb_section fb_built=&#8221;1&#8243; _builder_version=&#8221;4.18.0&#8243; _module_preset=&#8221;default&#8221; da_disable_devices=&#8221;off|off|off&#8221; locked=&#8221;off&#8221; global_colors_info=&#8221;{}&#8221; da_is_popup=&#8221;off&#8221; da_exit_intent=&#8221;off&#8221; da_has_close=&#8221;on&#8221; da_alt_close=&#8221;off&#8221; da_dark_close=&#8221;off&#8221; da_not_modal=&#8221;on&#8221; da_is_singular=&#8221;off&#8221; da_with_loader=&#8221;off&#8221; da_has_shadow=&#8221;on&#8221;][et_pb_row _builder_version=&#8221;4.18.0&#8243; _module_preset=&#8221;default&#8221; custom_padding=&#8221;45px||45px||true|&#8221; hover_enabled=&#8221;0&#8243; global_colors_info=&#8221;{}&#8221; sticky_enabled=&#8221;0&#8243;][et_pb_column type=&#8221;4_4&#8243; _builder_version=&#8221;4.18.0&#8243; _module_preset=&#8221;default&#8221; global_colors_info=&#8221;{}&#8221;][et_pb_text _builder_version=&#8221;4.18.0&#8243; _module_preset=&#8221;default&#8221; text_font=&#8221;|700|||||||&#8221; text_text_color=&#8221;gcid-c06f992e-1a1f-4a27-8457-39b06448a507&#8243; text_font_size=&#8221;28px&#8221; text_line_height=&#8221;1.5em&#8221; text_orientation=&#8221;center&#8221; hover_enabled=&#8221;0&#8243; global_colors_info=&#8221;{%22gcid-c06f992e-1a1f-4a27-8457-39b06448a507%22:%91%22text_text_color%22%93}&#8221; sticky_enabled=&#8221;0&#8243;]\n<p>PLOGG FOR THE PLANET<\/p>\n[\/et_pb_text][et_pb_text _builder_version=&#8221;4.18.0&#8243; _module_preset=&#8221;default&#8221; text_text_color=&#8221;#000000&#8243; text_font_size=&#8221;16px&#8221; text_line_height=&#8221;1.5em&#8221; text_orientation=&#8221;center&#8221; global_colors_info=&#8221;{}&#8221;]\n<p>Plogg for the Planet is an activity that combines physical exercise with environmental cleanup. The word &#8220;plogg&#8221; comes from the combination of &#8220;jogging&#8221; and &#8220;plocka upp&#8221; (Swedish for &#8220;pick up&#8221;), perfectly encapsulating the essence of this practice.<\/p>\n<p>During a Plogg for the Planet event, participants go out for a run or jog in natural areas, urban parks, or beaches, carrying bags or gloves to collect litter they encounter along the way. The idea is not only to improve participants&#8217; physical health but also to actively contribute to environmental conservation and the cleanliness of public spaces.<\/p>\n<p>This type of activity not only helps clean up the environment but also raises awareness about the impact of waste on nature and fosters a sense of environmental responsibility. Additionally, it&#8217;s an effective way to promote teamwork and community, as it can be done by people of all ages and abilities.<\/p>\n<p>Plogg for the Planet is more than just a sports activity; it&#8217;s a movement aimed at inspiring positive change in society, promoting more sustainable habits, and fostering a deeper connection with the environment.<\/p>\n[\/et_pb_text][\/et_pb_column][\/et_pb_row][et_pb_row _builder_version=&#8221;4.18.0&#8243; _module_preset=&#8221;default&#8221; global_colors_info=&#8221;{}&#8221;][et_pb_column type=&#8221;4_4&#8243; _builder_version=&#8221;4.18.0&#8243; _module_preset=&#8221;default&#8221; global_colors_info=&#8221;{}&#8221;][dsm_image_carousel gallery_ids=&#8221;38295,38294,38296,38297,38298,38299,38300&#8243; _builder_version=&#8221;4.18.0&#8243; _module_preset=&#8221;default&#8221; hover_enabled=&#8221;0&#8243; global_colors_info=&#8221;{}&#8221; sticky_enabled=&#8221;0&#8243;][\/dsm_image_carousel][\/et_pb_column][\/et_pb_row][\/et_pb_section]\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>PLOGG FOR THE PLANETPlogg for the Planet is an activity that combines physical exercise with environmental cleanup. The word &#8220;plogg&#8221; comes from the combination of &#8220;jogging&#8221; and &#8220;plocka upp&#8221; (Swedish for &#8220;pick up&#8221;), perfectly encapsulating the essence of this practice. During a Plogg for the Planet event, participants go out for a run or jog in natural areas, urban parks, or beaches, carrying bags or gloves to collect litter they encounter along the way. The idea is not only to improve participants&#8217; physical health but also to actively contribute to environmental conservation and the cleanliness of public spaces. This type of activity not only helps clean up the environment but also raises awareness about the impact of waste on nature and fosters a sense of environmental responsibility. Additionally, it&#8217;s an effective way to promote teamwork and community, as it can be done by people of all ages and abilities. Plogg for the Planet is more than just a sports activity; it&#8217;s a movement aimed at inspiring positive change in society, promoting more sustainable habits, and fostering a deeper connection with the environment.<div class=\"et_pb_module dsm_image_carousel dsm_image_carousel_0 dsm_image_carousel_arrow_outside dsm_image_carousel_arrow_mobile_inside \">\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"et_pb_module_inner\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"swiper-container dsm_image_carousel_container  dsm_image_carousel_carousel\" dir=\"ltr\"data-effect=\"default\"\n\t\t\tdata-slider-effect-shadows=\"false\"\n\t\t\tdata-slider-effect-coverflow-rotate=\"30\"\n\t\t\tdata-slider-effect-coverflow-depth=\"0\"\n\t\t\tdata-loop=\"true\"\n\t\t\tdata-slide-to-show=\"4\"\n\t\t\tdata-slide-to-show-tablet=\"1\"\n\t\t\tdata-slide-to-show-phone=\"1\"\n\t\t\tdata-slide-to-scroll=\"1\"\n\t\t\tdata-slide-to-scroll-tablet=\"1\"\n\t\t\tdata-slide-to-scroll-phone=\"1\"\n\t\t\tdata-space